\v 15 \w For|strong="G1063"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w great|strong="G3173"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w sight|strong="G1799"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w*; \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \nd \w must|strong="G4095"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w*\nd* \w drink|strong="G4095"\w* \w either|strong="G2532"\w* \w wine|strong="G3631"\w* \w or|strong="G2532"\w* \w strong|strong="G3173"\w* \w drink|strong="G4095"\w*;\f + \fr 1:15 \ft This sounds like a Nazirite—Numbers 6:3.\f* \w indeed|strong="G2532"\w*, \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w filled|strong="G4130"\w* \w with|strong="G1537"\w* \w Holy|strong="G4151"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w*\f + \fr 1:15 \ft Since ‘Holy Spirit’ occurs without a definite article, I take the phrase as a proper name.\f* already \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w his|strong="G2532"\w* \w mother|strong="G3384"\w*'\w s|strong="G2962"\w* \w womb|strong="G2836"\w*.
