\v 23 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w so|strong="G2532"\w*, \w when|strong="G5613"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w days|strong="G2250"\w* \w of|strong="G2250"\w* \w his|strong="G1519"\w* \w service|strong="G3009"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* fulfilled, \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w took|strong="G1096"\w* off \w for|strong="G1519"\w* \w home|strong="G3624"\w*.\f + \fr 1:23 \ft We know the time frame when it was the division of Abijah's turn to serve (for only two weeks). Assuming that Elizabeth became pregnant as soon as Zacharias got home, we may deduce that Jesus was born in September/October (six months after John).\f*
\p 
\v 24 \w Well|strong="G2532"\w* \w after|strong="G3326"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w days|strong="G2250"\w*\f + \fr 1:24 \ft Which ones? Presumably “the days of his service” in verse 23.\f* \w his|strong="G1438"\w* \w wife|strong="G1135"\w* \w Elizabeth|strong="G1665"\w* \w became|strong="G4815"\w* \w pregnant|strong="G4815"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* stayed \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w seclusion|strong="G4032"\w* \w five|strong="G4002"\w* \w months|strong="G3376"\w*.\f + \fr 1:24 \ft Her menopause was ancient history, so what was happening was ‘impossible’; besides, even if she was pregnant the likelihood of a miscarriage would be high; so she kept quiet. But after five months she would begin to ‘show’, and the prospect of success was good.\f* \w She|strong="G2532"\w* \w kept|strong="G2532"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*,
\v 25 “\w So|strong="G3779"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w*'\w s|strong="G2962"\w* \w what|strong="G3739"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w has|strong="G2962"\w* \w done|strong="G4160"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w days|strong="G2250"\w*\f + \fr 1:25 \ft A pregnancy involves a fair number of days, and divine intervention was necessary all the time to enable her to carry the baby to term.\f* \w when|strong="G1722"\w* \w He|strong="G3739"\w* concerned Himself \w to|strong="G1722"\w* \w take|strong="G1896"\w* away \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w reproach|strong="G3681"\w* \w among|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w people|strong="G4160"\w*!”\f + \fr 1:25 \ft At that time people looked down on a married woman who had no children.\f*
\ms1 The birth of Jesus foretold—5 \sc bc\sc*
\p 
\v 26 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w sixth|strong="G1623"\w* \w month|strong="G3376"\w*\f + \fr 1:26 \ft Of Elizabeth's pregnancy.\f* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* angel \w Gabriel|strong="G1043"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w sent|strong="G2316"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w a|strong="G1519"\w* \w town|strong="G4172"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w Galilee|strong="G1056"\w* \w named|strong="G3686"\w* Natsareth,\f + \fr 1:26 \ft For an explanation of this spelling, and its importance, please see the note at Matthew 2:23.\f*
\v 27 \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w virgin|strong="G3933"\w* \w betrothed|strong="G3423"\w*\f + \fr 1:27 \ft This involved a signed legal document, so much so that the couple were then called husband and wife, so ‘engaged’ (at least in contemporary society) is not an adequate rendering.\f* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w man|strong="G3739"\w* \w whose|strong="G3739"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w Joseph|strong="G2501"\w*, \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w house|strong="G3624"\w*\f + \fr 1:27 \ft See Luke 2:4.\f* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w David|strong="G1138"\w*; \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w virgin|strong="G3933"\w*'s \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w Mary|strong="G3137"\w*.
\v 28 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w upon|strong="G3588"\w* \w entering|strong="G1525"\w* where \w she|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* angel \w said|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w Rejoice|strong="G5463"\w*, recipient \w of|strong="G2532"\w* grace, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w*; blessed \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w among|strong="G4314"\w* women!”\f + \fr 1:28 \ft To be the mother of the Messiah was a blessing granted to only one woman in the whole history of this world (see Genesis 3:15). Less than 2% of the Greek manuscripts, of objectively inferior quality, omit ‘blessed are you among women’ (to be followed by NIV, NASB, LB, TEV, etc.).\f*
\v 29 \w But|strong="G1161"\w* \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* seeing \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w she|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w perplexed|strong="G1298"\w* \w at|strong="G1909"\w* \w his|strong="G1909"\w* \w word|strong="G3056"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* trying \w to|strong="G2532"\w* figure \w out|strong="G2532"\w* \w what|strong="G3588"\w* \w sort|strong="G4217"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* greeting \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w might|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w*.\f + \fr 1:29 \ft In Zacharias the angel inspired fear, but Mary sensed immediately that the angel did not represent a menace or threat and concentrated on his astounding words. In typical female fashion, she was trying to figure out the hidden agenda.\f*
\s1 Gabriel delivers
\p 
\v 30 \w The|strong="G2532"\w* angel \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w her|strong="G3137"\w*: “\w Do|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w afraid|strong="G5399"\w*,\f + \fr 1:30 \ft He is not telling her not to be afraid of himself, because she wasn't; I take it that he is telling her not to fear the future and the implications of his message.\f* \w Mary|strong="G3137"\w*, \w because|strong="G1063"\w* \w you|strong="G3004"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w found|strong="G2147"\w* \w favor|strong="G5485"\w* \w with|strong="G3844"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*.
\v 31 \w Now|strong="G2532"\w* \w then|strong="G2532"\w*, \w you|strong="G1722"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w conceive|strong="G4815"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w womb|strong="G1064"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w give|strong="G5088"\w* \w birth|strong="G5088"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w Son|strong="G5207"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G1722"\w* \w shall|strong="G2532"\w* \w call|strong="G2564"\w* \w His|strong="G1722"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w JESUS|strong="G2424"\w*.\f + \fr 1:31 \ft Although the angel presumably addressed Mary in Hebrew, when it came to pronouncing the name, he may well have used the Greek name as we know it. The precise sequence of sounds can be written and pronounced in Hebrew.\f*
\v 32 \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w great|strong="G3173"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w called|strong="G2564"\w* ‘\w Son|strong="G5207"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Most|strong="G5310"\w* \w High|strong="G5310"\w*’; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w give|strong="G1325"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w throne|strong="G2362"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w His|strong="G2532"\w* \w father|strong="G3962"\w* \w David|strong="G1138"\w*,\f + \fr 1:32 \ft Through Mary, Jesus received some of David's genes; David was literally His ancestor (see Mary's genealogy in Luke 3:23-38).\f*
\v 33 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w reign|strong="G2532"\w* \w over|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w house|strong="G3624"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jacob|strong="G2384"\w*\f + \fr 1:33 \ft The ‘house of Jacob’ is not the Church, but the unending Kingdom will include much more than just that ‘house’.\f* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* ages; \w indeed|strong="G2532"\w*, \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w His|strong="G1519"\w* kingdom \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w no|strong="G3756"\w* \w end|strong="G5056"\w*!”\f + \fr 1:33 \ft This world will come to an end, but not Christ's Kingdom. What the angel said to Mary was even more tremendous than what he said to Zacharias.\f*
\s1 Mary agrees
\p 
\v 34 \w So|strong="G1161"\w* \w Mary|strong="G3137"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* angel, “\w How|strong="G4459"\w* \w shall|strong="G3778"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w*, \w since|strong="G1893"\w* \w I|strong="G1161"\w* \w do|strong="G3004"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w know|strong="G1097"\w* \w a|strong="G1510"\w* \w man|strong="G3778"\w*?”\f + \fr 1:34 \ft Zacharias expressed doubt, but Mary simply requests some necessary information. She has understood that God wants her to be the Messiah's mother—she was doubtless highly intelligent and perceptive. (In the Bible the verb ‘to know’ is used to refer to sexual intercourse.).\f*
\v 35 \w In|strong="G1909"\w* answer \w the|strong="G2532"\w* angel \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w her|strong="G3588"\w*: “\w Holy|strong="G4151"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w*\f + \fr 1:35 \ft The Text does not have a definite article with ‘Holy Spirit’.\f* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w come|strong="G1904"\w* \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w power|strong="G1411"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Most|strong="G5310"\w* \w High|strong="G5310"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* hover \w over|strong="G1909"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w*; precisely \w for|strong="G1909"\w* \w this|strong="G3588"\w* \w reason|strong="G1352"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w holy|strong="G4151"\w* \w One|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w born|strong="G1080"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w called|strong="G2564"\w* ‘\w Son|strong="G5207"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*’!\f + \fr 1:35 \ft Literally so—the Holy Spirit supplied the genes that normally are supplied by a human father.\f*
\v 36 \w Furthermore|strong="G2532"\w*, \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w relative|strong="G4773"\w* \w Elizabeth|strong="G1665"\w*, \w she|strong="G2532"\w* \w has|strong="G3778"\w* \w actually|strong="G2532"\w* \w conceived|strong="G4815"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w son|strong="G5207"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w her|strong="G3708"\w* \w old|strong="G2532"\w* \w age|strong="G1094"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w now|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w sixth|strong="G1623"\w* \w month|strong="G3376"\w* \w for|strong="G1722"\w* \w her|strong="G3708"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w called|strong="G2564"\w* \w barren|strong="G4723"\w*;
\v 37 \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w any|strong="G3956"\w* \w word|strong="G4487"\w* spoken \w by|strong="G3844"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w be|strong="G3756"\w* possible.”
\v 38 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w Mary|strong="G3137"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w*: “\w Yes|strong="G1161"\w*, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1473"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w*'\w s|strong="G2962"\w* slave! \w Let|strong="G1096"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w happen|strong="G1096"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w according|strong="G2596"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w your|strong="G2962"\w* \w word|strong="G4487"\w*.”\f + \fr 1:38 \ft Mary had to understand the proposal and be in full agreement, or she would not have been a good mother.\f* \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* angel departed \w from|strong="G2532"\w* \w her|strong="G3708"\w*.
\s1 Mary visits Elizabeth
\p 
\v 39 \w Then|strong="G1161"\w* \w Mary|strong="G3137"\w* \w quickly|strong="G1722"\w* got ready \w and|strong="G1161"\w* \w went|strong="G4198"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w hill|strong="G3714"\w* \w country|strong="G3714"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w days|strong="G2250"\w*, \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w a|strong="G1519"\w* \w town|strong="G4172"\w* \w of|strong="G2250"\w* \w Judah|strong="G2455"\w*,
\v 40 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w entered|strong="G1525"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w house|strong="G3624"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w Zacharias|strong="G2197"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* saluted \w Elizabeth|strong="G1665"\w*.\f + \fr 1:40 \ft I take it that Mary understood that the angel's reference to Elizabeth was relevant to her.\f*
\v 41 \w Well|strong="G2532"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w happened|strong="G1096"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w Elizabeth|strong="G1665"\w* heard \w Mary|strong="G3137"\w*'s salutation \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w babe|strong="G1025"\w* bounced \w up|strong="G2532"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* down \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w her|strong="G3137"\w* \w womb|strong="G2836"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w Elizabeth|strong="G1665"\w* \w was|strong="G1096"\w* \w filled|strong="G4130"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w Holy|strong="G4151"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w*.
\s1 Elizabeth prophesies
\p 
\v 42 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w she|strong="G2532"\w* \w cried|strong="G2532"\w* \w out|strong="G2532"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w great|strong="G3173"\w* \w voice|strong="G2906"\w*\f + \fr 1:42 \ft To cry or call out suggests unusual volume by itself, so why add ‘with a great/loud voice’? Since she spoke under the Holy Spirit's control, there was probably an unusual quality to the voice, and the neighbors heard it.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w*: “\w Blessed|strong="G2127"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w among|strong="G1722"\w* \w women|strong="G1135"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w blessed|strong="G2127"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Fruit|strong="G2590"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w womb|strong="G2836"\w*!
\v 43 \w Why|strong="G2443"\w* \w am|strong="G1473"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w so|strong="G2443"\w* favored \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w mother|strong="G3384"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w*\f + \fr 1:43 \ft What Elizabeth is saying, inspired by the Holy Spirit, is that the Messiah is already in Mary's womb, as witnessed by baby John's reaction. There was no human way that Elizabeth could know of the angel's conversation with Mary. Her prophecy served as a tremendous confirmation and encouragement to Mary—I imagine that the Holy Spirit had fertilized her as soon as she said, “Yes”.\f* \w should|strong="G3588"\w* \w come|strong="G2064"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*?
\v 44 \w Yes|strong="G1063"\w* \w indeed|strong="G1063"\w*, \w because|strong="G1063"\w* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w sound|strong="G5456"\w* \w of|strong="G1722"\w* \w your|strong="G3708"\w* salutation \w came|strong="G1096"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w my|strong="G3708"\w* \w ears|strong="G3775"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w babe|strong="G1025"\w* bounced \w up|strong="G1519"\w* \w and|strong="G3708"\w* down \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w my|strong="G3708"\w* \w womb|strong="G2836"\w* \w for|strong="G1063"\w* joy.\f + \fr 1:44 \ft The clear implication is that baby John was aware, was already a person in the womb.\f*
\v 45 \w Blessed|strong="G3107"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w she|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w believed|strong="G4100"\w*, \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w fulfillment|strong="G5050"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w been|strong="G1510"\w* \w spoken|strong="G2980"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w her|strong="G3754"\w* \w from|strong="G3844"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w*.”\f + \fr 1:45 \ft She is stating that Mary had heard from God through the angel, although she had no human way of knowing anything about it.\f*
\s1 Mary worships
\p 
\v 46 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w Mary|strong="G3137"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w*:
\q1 “\w My|strong="G1473"\w* \w soul|strong="G5590"\w* magnifies \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w*,
\q2 
\v 47 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w has|strong="G2316"\w* exulted \w over|strong="G1909"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w Savior|strong="G4990"\w*,\f + \fr 1:47 \ft Mary declares her own need of a Savior.\f*
\q1 
\v 48 \w in|strong="G1909"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w He|strong="G3754"\w* paid \w attention|strong="G1914"\w*
\q2 \w to|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G3956"\w* \w humble|strong="G5014"\w* station \w of|strong="G1909"\w* \w His|strong="G3956"\w* slave (f).
\q1 \w Yes|strong="G1063"\w* \w indeed|strong="G1063"\w*, \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w from|strong="G3588"\w* \w now|strong="G3568"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w*
\q2 \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w generations|strong="G1074"\w* \w will|strong="G1473"\w* declare \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w to|strong="G1909"\w* \w be|strong="G3956"\w* highly favored,\f + \fr 1:48 \ft So it has been for 2000 years; in every generation there have been those who called her ‘blessed’.\f*
\q1 
\v 49 \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Mighty|strong="G1415"\w* \w One|strong="G3588"\w* \w did|strong="G4160"\w* sublime \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*,
\q2 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* Holy \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w His|strong="G4160"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w*.
\q1 
