\v 8 \w The|strong="G2532"\w* \w master|strong="G2962"\w* \w even|strong="G2532"\w* ‘\w commended|strong="G1867"\w*’ \w the|strong="G2532"\w* dishonest \w manager|strong="G3623"\w*, \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w had|strong="G2532"\w* \w acted|strong="G4160"\w* \w shrewdly|strong="G5430"\w*. \w The|strong="G2532"\w* \w sons|strong="G5207"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* age \w are|strong="G1510"\w* shrewder \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w their|strong="G1438"\w* \w own|strong="G1438"\w* \w generation|strong="G1074"\w* \w than|strong="G5228"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w sons|strong="G5207"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Light|strong="G5457"\w*.\f + \fr 16:8 \ft According to the value system of the world it is ‘smart’ to take advantage of other people, but those who follow the Light must be different. Of course the master's ‘commendation’ was sarcastic, since the dishonest manager still lost his job.\f*
\s2 A bit of irony
\p 
\v 9 “\w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w even|strong="G2532"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*, \w make|strong="G4160"\w* \w friends|strong="G5384"\w* \w for|strong="G1519"\w* \w yourselves|strong="G1438"\w* \w by|strong="G1537"\w* \w means|strong="G3004"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* unrighteous \w mammon|strong="G3126"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w whenever|strong="G3752"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w fail|strong="G1587"\w*, \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w receive|strong="G1209"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* eternal \w dwellings|strong="G4633"\w*!\f + \fr 16:9 \ft The use of sarcasm is not rare in the Bible, and here the Lord is clearly being sarcastic: getting into the eternal dwellings does not depend on ‘buying’ friends down here; it depends on pleasing the Owner up there. And of course, the dishonest friends will not even be there! Notice the reaction of the Pharisees in verse 14—I take it that verses 1-13 were mainly directed at them.\f*
\v 10 \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w faithful|strong="G4103"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w very|strong="G4183"\w* \w little|strong="G1646"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w faithful|strong="G4103"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w much|strong="G4183"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* dishonest \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w very|strong="G4183"\w* \w little|strong="G1646"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* dishonest \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w much|strong="G4183"\w*.
\v 11 \w If|strong="G1487"\w* \w therefore|strong="G3767"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w have|strong="G5210"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w been|strong="G1096"\w* \w faithful|strong="G4103"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* unrighteous \w mammon|strong="G3126"\w*, \w who|strong="G5101"\w* \w will|strong="G5101"\w* \w commit|strong="G3756"\w* \w to|strong="G1722"\w* \w your|strong="G1487"\w* \w trust|strong="G4100"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* genuine?\f + \fr 16:11 \ft Monetary value is the ‘very little’, and spiritual value is the ‘much’, the ‘genuine’.\f*
\v 12 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w been|strong="G1096"\w* \w faithful|strong="G4103"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w what|strong="G5101"\w* belongs \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w another|strong="G3588"\w*, \w who|strong="G5101"\w* \w will|strong="G5101"\w* \w give|strong="G1325"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w what|strong="G5101"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w your|strong="G5212"\w* own?
\v 13 \w No|strong="G3756"\w* \w servant|strong="G3610"\w* \w can|strong="G1410"\w* \w serve|strong="G1398"\w* \w two|strong="G1417"\w* \w masters|strong="G2962"\w*; \w either|strong="G2228"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w hate|strong="G3404"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* love \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w other|strong="G2087"\w*, \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* devoted \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w despise|strong="G2706"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w other|strong="G2087"\w*. \w You|strong="G2532"\w* \w cannot|strong="G1410"\w* \w serve|strong="G1398"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w mammon|strong="G3126"\w*!”\f + \fr 16:13 \ft Verse 13 declares a terribly important truth. To embrace the world's value system (humanism, relativism, materialism) is to reject God. Materialistic ‘Christians’ are really serving mammon (‘mammon’ includes more than just money).\f*
\s1 The Law will not fail
\p 
\v 14 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Pharisees|strong="G5330"\w*, \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w lovers|strong="G5366"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w money|strong="G5366"\w*, \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* listening \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3956"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* ridiculing \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*.
\v 15 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*: “\w You|strong="G5210"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w justify|strong="G1344"\w* \w yourselves|strong="G1438"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w men|strong="G3588"\w*, \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w knows|strong="G1097"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w hearts|strong="G2588"\w*. \w That|strong="G3754"\w* \w which|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w exalted|strong="G5308"\w* \w among|strong="G1722"\w* \w men|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w an|strong="G2532"\w* abomination \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*.\f + \fr 16:15 \ft There will not be any abomination in heaven—‘abomination’ is a strong term; do pause and ponder!\f*
\v 16 \w The|strong="G2532"\w* \w Law|strong="G3551"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Prophets|strong="G4396"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w until|strong="G3360"\w* \w John|strong="G2491"\w*; \w since|strong="G5119"\w* \w then|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* Kingdom \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w being|strong="G2532"\w* \w proclaimed|strong="G2097"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w one|strong="G3956"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* trying \w to|strong="G1519"\w* force \w his|strong="G1438"\w* \w way|strong="G3956"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w*.\f + \fr 16:16 \ft No one gets into the Kingdom on his own terms.\f*
\v 17 \w But|strong="G1161"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w easier|strong="G2123"\w* \w for|strong="G1161"\w* \w heaven|strong="G3772"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w pass|strong="G3928"\w* \w away|strong="G3928"\w*, \w than|strong="G2228"\w* \w for|strong="G1161"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w tittle|strong="G2762"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Law|strong="G3551"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w fail|strong="G4098"\w*.
\p 
\v 18 “\w Whoever|strong="G3956"\w* divorces \w his|strong="G3956"\w* \w wife|strong="G1135"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w marries|strong="G1060"\w* \w another|strong="G2087"\w* \w woman|strong="G1135"\w* \w commits|strong="G3431"\w* \w adultery|strong="G3431"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w whoever|strong="G3956"\w* \w marries|strong="G1060"\w* \w her|strong="G3956"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* divorced \w from|strong="G2532"\w* \w her|strong="G3956"\w* husband \w commits|strong="G3431"\w* \w adultery|strong="G3431"\w*.\f + \fr 16:18 \ft Now there you have a plain statement!\f*
\s1 A rich man and beggar Lazarus\f + \fr 16:19 \ft The Text does not state that this is a parable, so most probably it is not.\f*
\p 
\v 19 “\w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w certain|strong="G5100"\w* \w rich|strong="G4145"\w* \w man|strong="G5100"\w* \w who|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w dressed|strong="G1737"\w* \w in|strong="G2596"\w* \w purple|strong="G4209"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w fine|strong="G2532"\w* \w linen|strong="G1040"\w*, \w living|strong="G2165"\w* \w in|strong="G2596"\w* luxury \w every|strong="G2596"\w* \w day|strong="G2250"\w*.
\v 20 \w And|strong="G1161"\w* \w there|strong="G1161"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w a|strong="G1161"\w* \w certain|strong="G5100"\w* \w beggar|strong="G4434"\w* \w named|strong="G3686"\w* \w Lazarus|strong="G2976"\w*, \w covered|strong="G1669"\w* \w with|strong="G4314"\w* \w sores|strong="G1669"\w*, \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w had|strong="G3588"\w* \w been|strong="G5100"\w* placed \w at|strong="G4314"\w* \w his|strong="G4314"\w* \w gate|strong="G4440"\w*,
