\v 45 \w Then|strong="G5119"\w* \w He|strong="G3588"\w* \w opened|strong="G1272"\w* \w their|strong="G3588"\w* \w understanding|strong="G3563"\w* so \w as|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G3588"\w* comprehend \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w Scriptures|strong="G1124"\w*.
\v 46 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*: “\w Thus|strong="G3779"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w written|strong="G1125"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w thus|strong="G3779"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* necessary\f + \fr 24:46 \ft A mere handful (0.5%) of the Greek manuscripts, of objectively inferior quality, omit “and thus it was necessary” (as in NIV, NASB, LB, TEV, etc.).\f* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w suffer|strong="G3958"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w rise|strong="G2250"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w dead|strong="G3498"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w third|strong="G5154"\w* \w day|strong="G2250"\w*,
